<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://homepage.ntlworld.com/goth/traklair.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--> <br>
<br>
Okay, let me explain this a bit.<br>
<br>
Trakanon: He has two positions, marked 1 and 2 on the map. When he's in position 1 you're safe to pull. If you can't see his wing from the top left hand corner of the map (near the water), then hes in position 1. He moves roughly every 20 minutes.<br>
<br>
Protector: He wanders through those 3 positions, but not in that order. He might go from 1 to 3, then to 2 to 1, then to 2 to 3. Anything with three positions or more are like that. I've never bothered writing down the exact order.<br>
<br>
Brown Wandering Juggernaut: Also wanders through 3 positions.<br>
<br>
Blue Wandering Juggernaut: He goes back and fore between those two points. He tends to stay at position 1 more than number 2, but when he goes to 2, he tends to stay there a while.<br>
<br>
Okay, so how to do this:<br>
<br>
First, get DMF (Dead Man Floating), you're going to need it. Also get shrink (it makes you run faster) and/or Run Speed 3. It'll make things a whole lot safer on your poor head.<br>
<br>
When Trak is in the safe spot, run up to the X on the map and feign. This is a great spot to watch all the mobs moving around. What you need to do to get the protector out of there is have the Protector at position 1, the brown Jugg at position 2, and the blue Jugg at position 1.<br>
<br>
Rule number 1 about Trakanons lair, and something you must never forget. Never ever attack anything, it'll aggro Trakanon. For the Protector to chase you, you literally have to stand under its nose. Its got a VERY small aggro radius, so you have to run up there and stand under its nose until it gets annoyed at your presence. When hes following, float off the edge (you did remember DMF didn't you?), circle around over the water and float down toward the cavern entrance, where your raid group should be hiding further inside. This will stop the Protector from beating on you (he really hurts) and you can usually get to your raid team before he catches up with you.<br>
<br>
Kill the Protector and its onto the rest. Go back to your X on the map, watch and wait. When Brown Jugg is at 2 and Blue Jugg is at 2, run up and let Blue Jugg aggro on you. This will set off a chain reaction. Brown Jugg will be close enough to get annoyed, and also the stationary Jugg next to him will get annoyed, so you'll have all three remaining Juggernauts chasing you back to the raid camp. Again float off the edge over the water to avoid a beating.<br>
<br>
And there you go. You're all ready to kill Trakanon. Don't worry about the other two stationarys and the Froglok, they won't aggro you, they're too far away. Just make sure Trakanon doesn't gate. It happened to me one time and he gated right on top of the Froglok, aggroing them too. That was messy, but we won in the end. Always fight Trak in his cave, as far back as you can, near Position 1 marked on the map. And when you approach him, go over the rock, not around it, that helps too.<br>
<br>
The End. <br>
<br>
EDIT NOTE: Its been a while since I did it. You might need to do the Juggernauts first then the Protector, not the other way around. When you pull, never have anything at position 3. <p><center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=44191" target=blank>Aliera Fyrestrike</a><BR>Grandmaster Monk of Quellious - Morell Thule</center></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub38.ezboard.com/bmonklybusiness43508.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=alierafyrestrike>Aliera Fyrestrike</A> at: 5/10/02 12:08:49 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub38.ezboard.com/ukuzak155.showPublicProfile?language=EN>kuzak155</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(5/14/02 1:11:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=943.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Secret of Trakanons Lair</span><hr size=1> Good guide, thanks for helping out all the monks with no Trakky experience.<br>
<br>
Also, Shrink does NOT make you run faster.  It makes your shorter, which changes your vantage point, making it SEEM like you run faster.  If you don't believe me, create an ogre and run around a bit, then do the same with a halfling.  All level 1 characters move at the same speed, and yet it looks like the halfling is moving faster, doesn't it?<br>
<br>
