<br>
The other night myself and Defendant duo pulled the lair.  Def pulled the 2 roamer juggs without aggroing Trak or the Prot.  While the guild was fighting those 2 mobs, me still waiting in lair, saw my chance to grab the Prot when he moved forward.  I grabbed the Prot and took him back to the raid force.  So yes, it is possible to split off the other 2 juggs from the Prot.  And .. If you really know what you are doing, with a lil luck and a lot of timing you can split em off without even having to FD.  Just keep in mind those 2 other juggs are roamers so they will not lose aggro easy.  Just hope when you pop up out of FD, they are far enough away from Trak that when they go running after you, they don't bring that damn devil dragon with them.<br>
<br>
<br>
Being level 60 and knowing how to use aggro range pulling well helps a ton.  Not really much science to it on the surface, just inch up close enough to a mob till it sees you and attacks.  Then run like hell back to your raid party.<br>
<br>
